## 🚫 Infeasible Features & Critical Limitations

Due to design choices enforcing offline edge isolation, the following features **cannot be achieved**:
1.  **Real-World Global Forecasting**: The bot has no access to the live internet. It cannot query weather in New York, London, or other external locations. If asked, the bot will explicitly refuse, stating it only has access to local station data.
2.  **Zero-Latency LLM Inference on Pi 4 Hardware**: While the heuristic NLP engine and GNN inference take <10ms, running Llama models (even quantized 3B versions) directly on a Raspberry Pi 4 is extremely slow. A hardware accelerator (like a TPU or external server loopback) is required for real-time natural language synthesis.
3.  **Complex NLP Semantic Comprehension on Heuristics**: The intent parser (`nlp_engine.py`) uses fast regex maps to reduce latency. It will fail on complex double negatives or extremely slang-heavy queries unless supplemented by the local LLM.

